# Frontend UI Library Rule

Use Material UI (MUI) for UI components and `@mui/icons-material` for icons.

## Guidelines
- Prefer MUI components (`@mui/material`) over custom HTML for consistency and accessibility.
- Use theme tokens; avoid hard-coded colors/sizes. Configure theme at app root.
- Icons must come from `@mui/icons-material` (or `@mui/icons-material/*`).
- Avoid mixing multiple UI libraries in the same view.

## Setup
- Ensure MUI is installed:
  - `@mui/material`
  - `@emotion/react`
  - `@emotion/styled`
  - `@mui/icons-material`
- Provide the theme via `ThemeProvider` in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx).

## Examples
- Buttons: `import { Button } from '@mui/material'`
- Icons: `import LoginIcon from '@mui/icons-material/Login'`